LOS ANGELES (Zap2it.com) It looks like we can finally close the book on the past week of &ldquo;As &#8216;CSI&rsquo; Turns.&rdquo;
CBS and &ldquo;CSI&rdquo; star George Eads reached an agreement Friday (July 23) that will allow Eads back on the series, a little more than a week after he was fired in a contract dispute.
So, despite much back-and-forth talk about contracts and oversleeping and the like, it turns out television&rsquo;s highest-rated drama series will begin its fifth season with cast intact.

In his first public appearance since being fired from CBS&rsquo; hit drama &ldquo;CSI: Crime Scene Investigation,&rdquo; George Eads called his dismissal &ldquo;a misunderstanding.&rdquo;
Meanwhile, sources said CBS was in talks with Jorja Fox, the other &ldquo;CSI&rdquo; co-star who was let go last week after what CBS executives characterized as their failure to show up for work as scheduled after they&rsquo;d made demands for salary increases (HR 7&frasl;16).
